-- The inline consensus fold — identity-routed, dedup-first, native.
--
-- NATIVE (2026-07-21, GH #565): the body lives in C (src/fold_route.c).
-- Consensus is content: dedup it the way ingest dedups entities. The batch is
-- split by what it IS, per relation type:
--   * EXISTING cells  -> bulk UPDATE, re-fold against current state;
--   * NOVEL cells     -> bulk INSERT; INSERT tuple-routes to the one owning
--                        leaf, and NOT EXISTS (literal type -> pruned) proves
--                        novelty, so there is NO conflict to arbitrate.
--
-- History of the SQL forms this replaces (all measured, kept so nobody
-- re-tries them):
--  * MERGE: fans out across ALL consensus leaves because the partition key is
--    a runtime join value (2026-07-16, the CILI 7-minute peg).
--  * per-type loop re-unnesting the FULL arrays each iteration: O(2·N·T)
--    materializations (21s insert / 60s re-fold at N=200k,T=10).
--  * BATCH-ONCE temp table (2026-07-16): correct and O(N) — but still a fresh
--    CREATE TEMP TABLE + CREATE INDEX + ANALYZE on every call, and generic
--    per-type statements re-planned per call.
--
-- The native routing groups the batch by type in C and executes SESSION-CACHED
-- prepared plans per type whose type_id is a LITERAL in the plan text (HTAB of
-- type -> SPI_keepplan'd plan in TopMemoryContext): LIST pruning once per
-- (backend, type) reused across every call, HASH pruning per row, no temp
-- table, no ANALYZE, no re-plan.
--
-- One implementation per fact, preserved:
--  * the Glicko fold runs in the SAME native scalar the plpgsql called
--    (laplace_glicko2_accumulate_games), once per row, record-valued — the
--    rating period IS the batch;
--  * cell ids are computed in C through the SAME core hash the SQL
--    consensus_id() wraps — blake3(subject || type || COALESCE(object, 16 zero
--    bytes)) — byte-identical layout;
--  * the duplicate-cell contract check raises the same cardinality_violation.
--
-- NO mask queue here: the caller deposits highway bits INLINE for this same
-- delta (highway_mask_deposit); highway_mask_dirty is populated only by the
-- repair verbs, which need to CLEAR bits (per-source evict) — something an
-- OR-accumulate deposit cannot express.
--
-- Contract with the caller (ConsensusAccumulatingWriter) — unchanged:
--   * arrays are parallel and CLIENT-DEDUPED per call — one row per
--     (subject, type, object) cell;
--   * phi is uniform per cell per call (the writer's merge invariant);
--   * rows arrive sorted by (type, subject, id) — partition-key order; the
--     router only needs same-type rows ADJACENT and remains correct (merely
--     one extra plan execution) if they are not.
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION consensus_upsert(
    p_subjects bytea[],
    p_types    bytea[],
    p_objects  bytea[],
    p_phis     bigint[],
    p_games    bigint[],
    p_sums     bigint[],
    p_ts       timestamptz[])
    RETURNS bigint
    AS 'MODULE_PATHNAME', 'pg_laplace_consensus_upsert'
    LANGUAGE C VOLATILE;
